    heading: "Problem Statement"
    paragraphs:
      - "22% increase in non-new booking calls to the Contact Centre (approximately 10 full-time employees) in the YTD for the UK, reducing outbound call capability to high-risk customers."
      - "No existing tooling analyses call purpose or root cause beyond agent surveys and no action plan exists to reduce volume."

  - number: "02"
    heading: "The Solution"
    paragraphs:
      - "E2E call transcription pipeline (AWS) that ingests, transcribes and applies LLM analysis to surface the true drivers behind calls."
      - "Integration with Salesforce data to map calls to specific customers, developing a clear map of common customer touch points between booking and job completion."
      - "Newly defined global call categories and associated action plans for those calls that can be automated/deflected."

  - number: "03"
    heading: "Impact"
    list:
      - "Uncovered clear opportunities for automation through the customer self-service portal, targeting a reduction in call volumes of 10%."
      - "Scaled capability to four new business units (UK, Australia, New Zealand, Italy) following buy-in from Global Contact Centre Leads."
      - "Global alignment on 10 call categorisations, allowing for consistent reporting across business units."
      - "Built Business Case for 2027, identifying common pitfalls across business units and quantifying those with largest potential ROI through automation."

